01:25.486 --> 01:29.557
- RELAX AND COUNT BACKWARDS
FROM TEN, MR. KINNEY.

02:07.928 --> 02:11.131
- [grunting]

02:25.813 --> 02:28.582
- BRIAN--
- DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

02:28.616 --> 02:30.651
- LOOK, I'M SURE IT'S JUST
A TEMPORARY MALFUNCTION.

02:30.684 --> 02:33.254
IT TAKES TIME FOR YOUR BODY
TO HEAL ITSELF

02:33.287 --> 02:35.289
AND FOR YOU TO REGAIN
YOUR STRENGTH.

02:35.323 --> 02:36.790
BE PATIENT.

02:36.824 --> 02:40.461
EVERYTHING WILL BE UP
AND RUNNING IN NO TIME.

02:40.494 --> 02:44.565
- THANKS FOR NOT
SAYING ANYTHING.

02:49.570 --> 02:51.439
- I WANT TO GET
THOSE COOL PUMAS

02:51.472 --> 02:53.941
AND A PAIR OF DIESEL JEANS,
MAYBE TWO.

02:53.974 --> 02:55.409
- HEY, HEY.

02:55.443 --> 02:56.944
WHAT DO YOU THINK I AM,
MADE OF MONEY?

02:56.977 --> 02:58.579
- LIKE, YEAH.

02:58.612 --> 03:00.414
YOU'RE HAVING A MOVIE MADE.

03:00.448 --> 03:01.949
- WE HOPE.
AND I DIDN'T WORK MY ASS OFF

03:01.982 --> 03:04.952
SO I COULD PUT EXPENSIVE JEANS
ON YOURS.

03:04.985 --> 03:07.321
- BEN, I WANT TO GET
A COUPLE PAIRS OF DIESEL JEANS.

03:07.355 --> 03:09.957
- PULL UP YOUR PANTS.
I CAN SEE YOUR SHORTS.

03:09.990 --> 03:11.592
- THAT'S THE FUCKING POINT.

03:11.625 --> 03:13.494
- WE'RE TAKING HUNTER
TO BUY SOME NEW CLOTHES.

03:13.527 --> 03:14.995
- AND HAVE PIZZA AND GO
TO A MOVIE.

03:15.028 --> 03:17.765
- NOT A BRETT KELLER MOVIE.

03:17.798 --> 03:20.734
SO TOMORROW NIGHT?
THE MALL? THE THREE OF US?

03:20.768 --> 03:22.436
- UH, SURE. FINE.
[cell phone rings]

03:22.470 --> 03:24.338
AH, MUST BE MARK BLUESTEIN.
HE HAS THE FLU.

03:24.372 --> 03:26.240
I SAID I'D COVER HIS CLASS.

03:26.274 --> 03:28.509
HELLO?

03:28.542 --> 03:31.579
HEY.

03:31.612 --> 03:33.847
UH-HUH.

03:33.881 --> 03:35.849
SURE.

03:35.883 --> 03:38.386
UH, BREAKFAST, LUNCH,
WHATEVER.

03:38.419 --> 03:41.455
YEAH, SEE YOU THEN.

03:41.489 --> 03:42.856
- FOR SOMEBODY WHO'S LAID UP
WITH FLU,

03:42.890 --> 03:44.392
HE HAS
A PRETTY HEALTHY APPETITE.

03:44.425 --> 03:45.593
- OH, YEAH, THAT WASN'T MARK.

03:45.626 --> 03:46.860
IT WAS ANTHONY,
FROM THE LIBRARY.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.729
YOU REMEMBER,
I TOLD YOU ABOUT HIM?

03:48.762 --> 03:50.631
- YEAH, HOW COULD I FORGET?
HE ONLY CALLS YOU EVERY HOUR.

03:50.664 --> 03:52.600
- [scoffs]
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

03:52.633 --> 03:54.735
- MAYBE HE HAS A CRUSH ON YOU.
- THAT'S NOT TRUE EITHER.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.737
HE'S JUST A NICE KID
WHO WANTS TO BE A WRITER.

03:56.770 --> 03:59.773
WE GET TOGETHER
AND DISCUSS BOOKS, THAT'S ALL.

03:59.807 --> 04:01.509
SO TOMORROW NIGHT.

04:01.542 --> 04:04.345
PIZZA, MOVIE,
AND DIESEL JEANS.

04:04.378 --> 04:05.379
- TIGHT.

04:05.413 --> 04:09.016
- YEAH, YOU MEAN, "LOOSE."

04:09.049 --> 04:13.787
[both groaning]

04:30.103 --> 04:31.805
- OH, TOUCHDOWN!

04:31.839 --> 04:37.645
[laughing]

04:37.678 --> 04:41.649
MY, HOW THE BOY CAN SCORE.

04:41.682 --> 04:44.051
- I GOT A GOOD KICKER.

04:44.084 --> 04:45.919
- I'LL SAY.

04:45.953 --> 04:49.423
- THAT'S A QUARTERBACK'S
SECRET WEAPON.

04:51.091 --> 04:53.827
- SPEAKING OF SECRETS...

04:53.861 --> 04:55.396
DOES YOUR FIANCEE KNOW?

04:55.429 --> 04:57.398
- KNOW WHAT?

04:57.431 --> 04:59.533
- THAT YOU'RE...MM?

04:59.567 --> 05:01.402
- THAT I'M--

05:01.435 --> 05:03.437
- DO I REALLY HAVE TO SAY IT?

05:03.471 --> 05:05.406
THAT YOU'RE, UH, THE "H" WORD.

05:05.439 --> 05:07.575
- HARD-BODIED?

05:07.608 --> 05:09.810
HOT?
HUNG?

05:09.843 --> 05:11.545
YEAH, SHE KNOWS ALL THAT.

05:11.579 --> 05:13.447
- I MEANT, UH, HOMOSEXUAL.

05:13.481 --> 05:14.848
GAY. QUEER.

05:14.882 --> 05:18.419
- HEY, I'M NOT A FAG.

05:18.452 --> 05:20.454
- DID I USE THAT WORD?

05:20.488 --> 05:25.025
- A FAG IS
A SISSY, GIRL, A PANSY.

05:25.058 --> 05:27.094
YOU THINK I'M THAT?
- HARDLY.

05:27.127 --> 05:28.629
- A FAG CAN'T EVEN THROW
A BALL.

05:28.662 --> 05:29.963
DO YOU KNOW HOW FAR
I CAN THROW?

05:29.997 --> 05:32.433
- I RECKON A COUNTRY MILE.

05:32.466 --> 05:34.435
- I'M A HERO TO MILLIONS.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.003
NAME ONE FAG WHO'S A HERO.

05:36.036 --> 05:37.971
NAME ONE FAG WHO'S GOT A CALL
FROM THE PRESIDENT

05:38.005 --> 05:40.107
SAYING, "GREAT GAME."

05:40.140 --> 05:43.010
NAME ONE FAG THAT'S FUCKED
EVERY DALLAS CHEERLEADER,

05:43.043 --> 05:46.914
AND I DON'T EVEN PLAY
FOR DALLAS.

05:46.947 --> 05:50.050
NAME ONE FAG EVERY KID WANTS
TO GROW UP TO BE.

05:50.083 --> 05:52.920
- HARVEY FIERSTEIN?

05:52.953 --> 05:55.456
- SO WHY WOULD ANYONE THINK
I WAS A FAG?

05:55.489 --> 06:00.461
- MAYBE BECAUSE YOU HAD
YOUR DICK UP MY ASS?

06:00.494 --> 06:02.930
- SO I LIKE TO FUCK GUYS.

06:02.963 --> 06:05.866
DOESN'T MEAN THAT I LOVE THEM
OR WANT TO KISS THEM

06:05.899 --> 06:08.869
OR EVEN KNOW THEM.

06:08.902 --> 06:12.540
THIS IS JUST FOR FUN.
TO GET OFF.

06:12.573 --> 06:15.609
AND NO ONE'S TO EVER HEAR
ABOUT THIS.

06:15.643 --> 06:18.746
UNDERSTAND?

06:18.779 --> 06:22.950
- WHO'D BELIEVE ME
IF I TOLD THEM?

06:22.983 --> 06:27.421
- NEXT WEEK, AN ENORMOUS
250-FOOT MURAL OF YOURS

06:27.455 --> 06:29.557
WILL BE UNVEILED
AT PENN PLAZA.

06:29.590 --> 06:33.561
TOMORROW, AN EXHIBITION
OF YOUR DRAWINGS OPENS HERE,

06:33.594 --> 06:35.663
AT THE SIDNEY BLOOM GALLERY.

06:35.696 --> 06:37.431
TELL ME, MR. AUERBACH,

06:37.465 --> 06:39.099
WHY DID YOU CHOOSE PITTSBURGH?

06:39.132 --> 06:40.768
- WELL, UNLESS YOU'RE
A PIRATES FAN,

06:40.801 --> 06:43.036
THERE'S NOT A GODDAMN REASON
TO COME HERE.

06:43.070 --> 06:45.038
NOW THERE WILL BE.
- THAT'S PERFECT.

06:45.072 --> 06:47.708
- I'VE HEARD YOUR EGO
IS AS BIG AS YOUR MURAL.

06:47.741 --> 06:50.177
- I HOPE
I HAVEN'T LET YOU DOWN.

06:50.210 --> 06:52.446
I MEAN...I HOPE
THIS BAGEL-DEPRIVED BURG

06:52.480 --> 06:55.849
FEELS THE SAME WAY
WHEN THEY SEE MY WORK.

06:55.883 --> 06:58.118
- I THINK THAT'S ALL WE NEED.
THAT'S GOOD.

06:58.151 --> 07:00.988
THAT WAS GREAT.
THANK YOU.

07:01.021 --> 07:03.824
- ANY TIME, HONEY.

07:06.159 --> 07:09.663
HOW WAS I?
- OKAY, I GUESS.

07:09.697 --> 07:12.199
I WASN'T REALLY LISTENING.
I WAS WORKING.

07:12.232 --> 07:14.067
- I'M GLAD
I DIDN'T DISTRACT YOU.

07:14.101 --> 07:18.205
- NOT AT ALL.

07:18.238 --> 07:20.474
- YOU KNOW...
[chuckles]

07:20.508 --> 07:25.078
I HAVE THIS STRANGE FEELING
THAT I'M BEING...IGNORED.

07:25.112 --> 07:26.680
STRANGE, BECAUSE, I MEAN,
LET'S--LET'S FACE IT,

07:26.714 --> 07:28.215
I'M NOT USED TO BEING IGNORED.

07:28.248 --> 07:30.951
IN FACT, I THINK THE LAST TIME
IT HAPPENED, I WAS 14.

07:30.984 --> 07:33.220
SUZIE SCHROEDER WAS HER NAME.
- OH.

07:33.253 --> 07:34.888
- SHE DITCHED ME
AT A TASTEE FREEZ

07:34.922 --> 07:38.759
FOR A GUY WITH A TRIPLE SCOOP.

07:38.792 --> 07:40.628
BROKE MY HEART.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.095
- WELL, YOU NEEDN'T WORRY.

07:42.129 --> 07:44.965
I HAVEN'T BEEN
TO A TASTEE FREEZ IN YEARS.

07:44.998 --> 07:46.634
SO WHY DON'T YOU GO OVER
AND FLIRT

07:46.667 --> 07:50.037
WITH THAT NICE GIRL REPORTER
AND LEAVE ME TO MY WORK?

07:55.275 --> 07:56.777
[phone rings]

07:56.810 --> 07:59.780
- HARVEY, WHEN HAVE I EVER
LET YOU DOWN?

07:59.813 --> 08:01.114
- ARE YOU FUCKING KIDDING ME?

08:01.148 --> 08:02.850
- NAME ONE TIME.
- THE TIME I ASKED YOU

08:02.883 --> 08:04.251
OUT ON A DATE, AND YOU SAID,
"THANKS, BUT NO."

08:04.284 --> 08:05.986
- OKAY, NAME A SECOND.

08:06.019 --> 08:07.921
- OH, JESUS, BRIAN, I WAS ONE
OF YOUR FIRST CLIENTS.

08:07.955 --> 08:09.590
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE
A BIG SHOT NOW...

08:09.623 --> 08:12.259
[phone rings]
- HOLD ON.

08:12.292 --> 08:14.127
MR. DECARLO,
SORRY TO KEEP YOU.

08:14.161 --> 08:15.863
- WHEN IS THAT CAMPAIGN
GONNA BE READY?

08:15.896 --> 08:17.197
- WE'RE RIGHT ON SCHEDULE.

08:17.230 --> 08:19.132
- HOW DOES IT LOOK?
- IT LOOKS GREAT.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.134
- I NEED IT FOR
THE NEXT STOCKHOLDERS' MEETING.

08:21.168 --> 08:23.537
- WHEN?
- FRIDAY, 3:00,

08:23.571 --> 08:25.606
OR THEY'LL HAVE MY BALLS.
- HOLD ON.

08:25.639 --> 08:28.141
[beep]

08:28.175 --> 08:30.210
TELL JACOB THAT IF THE ART
FOR DANDY LUBE

08:30.243 --> 08:32.212
ISN'T ON MY DESK
BY 9:00 A.M. FRIDAY,

08:32.245 --> 08:33.881
HE'LL BE TEACHING
REMEDIAL FINGER PAINTING

08:33.914 --> 08:37.217
TO KINDERGARTNERS.

08:37.250 --> 08:41.154
MR. DECARLO, HOW DOES 10:00 A.M.
FRIDAY SOUND?

08:41.188 --> 08:42.890
- STILL HAVE MY BALLS.

08:42.923 --> 08:44.758
[beep]

08:44.792 --> 08:46.760
[phone rings]

08:46.794 --> 08:48.629
- HARVEY, DID YOU THINK
OF A SECOND?

08:48.662 --> 08:50.764
- ACTUALLY, NO.
- SEE? I TOLD YOU.

08:50.798 --> 08:52.633
- LOOK, YOU OWE ME BIG, BRIAN.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M SUPPOSED--

08:52.666 --> 08:55.168
- NOW STOP WORRYING,
I'LL GET YOU THE BACK COVER.

08:55.202 --> 08:58.105
- I'M COUNTING ON YOU,
HOT SHOT.

08:58.138 --> 09:00.674
- JEEZ, WITH AN ACT LIKE THAT,
YOU SHOULD BE IN VEGAS

09:00.708 --> 09:03.777
MAKING TIGERS VANISH
INTO THIN AIR.

09:03.811 --> 09:05.078
- THROW ME A BONE.

09:05.112 --> 09:09.116
I'M TRYING TO JUGGLE 15 BALLS
AT ONCE.

09:09.149 --> 09:10.918
NO REMARKS.

09:10.951 --> 09:12.319
THAT'S A NICE SUIT.

09:12.352 --> 09:18.058
- YEAH? WORKED WONDERS
ON SON OF DANDY LUBE.

09:18.091 --> 09:20.728
- YOU KNOW, I LIKE YOUR NEWFOUND
SELF-CONFIDENCE, THEODORE.

09:20.761 --> 09:23.130
FAR PREFERABLE
TO YOUR FORMER LACK THEREOF.

09:23.163 --> 09:25.599
- SO WHAT'S MY NEXT ASSIGNMENT,
JIM?

09:25.633 --> 09:27.000
- CONGRATS.

09:27.034 --> 09:29.136
BROWN ATHLETICS IS COMMITTING
A COOL MIL

09:29.169 --> 09:31.605
TO SNAG A MODEL
FOR THEIR NEW UNDERWEAR LINE.

09:31.639 --> 09:33.340
- WELL, AS LUCK WOULD HAVE IT,
I'M AVAILABLE.

09:33.373 --> 09:35.075
- UNFORTUNATELY,
THEY'RE LOOKING FOR SOMEONE

09:35.108 --> 09:36.209
WITH A HIGHER PROFILE.

09:36.243 --> 09:37.878
- NOT TO MENTION
A BIGGER BASKET.

09:37.911 --> 09:39.947
- THEY WANT
A FAMOUS SPORTS FIGURE.

09:39.980 --> 09:42.149
- I HAPPEN TO BE
PITTSBURGH'S 1986 JUNIOR CLASS

09:42.182 --> 09:43.684
PING-PONG CHAMPION.

09:43.717 --> 09:46.219
WELL, RUNNER-UP.

09:46.253 --> 09:48.355
- SO AT WHAT HOUR OF THE DAY
OR NIGHT

09:48.388 --> 09:51.358
AM I SUPPOSED TO CONDUCT
THIS STAR SEARCH?

09:51.391 --> 09:53.861
- I'LL DO IT FOR YOU, BRI.

09:53.894 --> 09:56.897
- YOU?
- YEAH.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.699
I LANDED DANDY LUBE,
DIDN'T I?

09:58.732 --> 10:01.268
LOOK, I'LL TALK TO SOME AGENTS,
A FEW MANAGERS,

10:01.301 --> 10:03.236
SEE WHO'S INTERESTED,
THEN PUT TOGETHER A SHORT LIST.

10:03.270 --> 10:04.404
FINAL DRAFT CHOICE,
OF COURSE, IS YOURS.

10:04.437 --> 10:05.839
- YEAH, THAT SOUNDS PERFECT,

10:05.873 --> 10:07.274
EXCEPT FOR
ONE ITTY-BITTY DETAIL.

10:07.307 --> 10:09.710
YOU DON'T KNOW A FUCKING THING
ABOUT SPORTS.

10:09.743 --> 10:11.144
- BUT I KNOW ABOUT SEX,

10:11.178 --> 10:13.246
WHAT LOOKS GOOD
IN A PAIR OF SHORTS.

10:13.280 --> 10:15.282
AFTER ALL, I AM A GAY MAN,

10:15.315 --> 10:18.752
AND SEX IS
OUR NATIONAL PASTIME.

10:22.222 --> 10:26.193
- THESE DRAWINGS OF RAGE
AND JT ARE HOT.

10:26.226 --> 10:28.896
WHY CAN'T WE EVER SEE ZEPHYR
IN A FUCK-FEST

10:28.929 --> 10:30.731
WITH SOME GREAT-LOOKING GUY?

10:30.764 --> 10:33.767
- BECAUSE NOBODY BUYS OUR COMICS
TO SEE ZEPHYR GET LAID.

10:33.801 --> 10:35.135
- THAT IS SO NOT TRUE

10:35.168 --> 10:36.804
JUST BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT
TO SEE IT.

10:36.837 --> 10:39.272
- IT'S NOT THAT I DON'T WANT
TO SEE IT.

10:39.306 --> 10:41.041
IT'S THAT I CAN'T IMAGINE IT.

10:41.074 --> 10:42.409
- WELL, I CAN.

10:42.442 --> 10:44.011
WHEN HE AND HIS HUNKY BOYFRIEND,

10:44.044 --> 10:45.312
THE WORLD-FAMOUS PALEONTOLOGIST,

10:45.345 --> 10:47.014
PROFESSOR KEN KIRSCHNER,
GET IT ON,

10:47.047 --> 10:52.419
THEY REALLY RATTLE
THE OLD DINOSAUR BONES.

10:52.452 --> 10:54.788
EXCEPT EVER SINCE
THE SCIENTIFIC COMMUNITY

10:54.822 --> 10:58.291
REJECTED THE PROFESSOR'S
LATEST RESEARCH FINDINGS,

10:58.325 --> 11:00.994
THEY HAVEN'T FELT MUCH LIKE
DOING IT.

11:01.028 --> 11:03.163
- I KNOW WHAT THAT'S LIKE.

11:03.196 --> 11:06.033
JT HASN'T GOTTEN A RISE
OUT OF RAGE

11:06.066 --> 11:10.938
SINCE ICE TEENA ZAPPED HIM
WITH HER RADIATION GUN.

11:10.971 --> 11:11.972
- YOU MEAN--

11:12.005 --> 11:14.441
- NOT SINCE THE OPERATION.

11:14.474 --> 11:16.243
- BUT I THOUGHT THE DOCTOR
SAID THAT...

11:16.276 --> 11:18.045
- NOTHING WOULD BE AFFECTED?

11:18.078 --> 11:22.482
YEAH, WELL, SOMETHING
SURE AS HELL ISN'T WORKING.

11:22.515 --> 11:24.384
- MAYBE HE JUST NEEDS
SOME VIAGRA.

11:24.417 --> 11:28.455
- YOU TRY TELLING HIM THAT.

11:28.488 --> 11:31.058
- OKAY, SO HOW ABOUT WE TAKE
A LITTLE TRIP TO CHINATOWN?

11:31.091 --> 11:32.793
- I ALREADY ATE.

11:32.826 --> 11:34.828
- I MEANT TO SEE MASTER NEE.

11:34.862 --> 11:36.830
- WHO'S HE?

11:36.864 --> 11:38.465
- HE'S THIS HERBALIST
BEN SEES.

11:38.498 --> 11:40.333
HE SAYS HE'S A MIRACLE WORKER.

11:40.367 --> 11:41.802
HE GAVE HIM THIS STUFF
THAT ACTUALLY HELPED

11:41.835 --> 11:43.270
LOWER HIS VIRAL LOAD.

11:43.303 --> 11:45.205
- COME ON, YOU DON'T ACTUALLY
BELIEVE THAT.

11:45.238 --> 11:48.208
- CHINESE MEDICINE'S BEEN
WORKING FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS.

11:48.241 --> 11:49.843
WHO AM I TO DOUBT IT?

11:49.877 --> 11:52.212
BESIDES, IF HE CAN HELP LOWER
BEN'S COUNT,

11:52.245 --> 11:55.816
MAYBE HE'LL BE ABLE TO RAISE...

11:55.849 --> 11:59.853
- THE TITANIC?

11:59.887 --> 12:01.388
- I GIVE THEM AN ASSIGNMENT

12:01.421 --> 12:03.423
TO CRITIQUE ONE
OF TENNESSEE WILLIAMS' PLAYS,

12:03.456 --> 12:04.992
AND WHAT DO THEY DO?

12:05.025 --> 12:08.996
THEY RIP HIM TO SHREDS,
LIKE A PACK OF JACKALS.

12:09.029 --> 12:11.098
- OH, YOU KNOW
HOW SOME QUEERS ARE.

12:11.131 --> 12:12.432
THEY'RE NOT CONTENT
TO CRITICIZE,

12:12.465 --> 12:15.368
THEY HAVE TO SEEK AND DESTROY.

12:15.402 --> 12:19.506
- ALL I KNOW IS, IT'S A LOT
HARDER TO CREATE SOMETHING

12:19.539 --> 12:21.975
THAN IT IS TO TEAR IT APART.

12:22.009 --> 12:24.377
- LIKE YOUR BOOK.

12:24.411 --> 12:27.247
THAT MUST'VE BEEN
LIKE GIVING BIRTH.

12:27.280 --> 12:29.149
- MOST PEOPLE HAVE NO IDEA.

12:29.182 --> 12:30.851
- I DO.

12:30.884 --> 12:35.522
EVERY SENTENCE I WRITE,
OR TRY TO, IS AGONY.

12:35.555 --> 12:37.424
I DON'T KNOW WHY I DO IT.

12:37.457 --> 12:38.859
- PROBABLY FOR THE SAME REASON
I DO,

12:38.892 --> 12:40.994
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE.

12:41.028 --> 12:43.130
IF YOU EVER WANT ME
TO READ ANYTHING,

12:43.163 --> 12:47.400
A STORY,
CHAPTER, SENTENCE...

12:47.434 --> 12:50.037
JUST ASK.
I PROMISE TO BE GENTLE.

12:50.070 --> 12:53.173
- I'M SURE YOU WOULD BE.

12:53.206 --> 12:57.044
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT EDMUND WHITE?

12:57.077 --> 13:00.447
- WHY, HIS ESSAYS AND ARTICLES
ON BEING POSITIVE

13:00.480 --> 13:02.883
INFLUENCED ME TREMENDOUSLY.

13:02.916 --> 13:06.019
BUT I PARTICULARLY LOVE
HIS AUTOBIOGRAPHICAL FICTION.

13:06.053 --> 13:07.454
IN FACT, A BOY'S OWN STORY

13:07.487 --> 13:10.423
INSPIRED ME TO WRITE R-U-1-2.

13:10.457 --> 13:14.327
- THEN HOW ABOUT COMING WITH ME
TO HIS LECTURE TOMORROW NIGHT?

13:14.361 --> 13:16.163
I'VE GOT AN EXTRA TICKET.

13:16.196 --> 13:19.332
- YOU KNOW, I...I WOULD LOVE TO,

13:19.366 --> 13:21.068
BUT, UH, I ALREADY MADE PLANS

13:21.101 --> 13:23.570
WITH MY PARTNER
AND OUR FOSTER SON.

13:23.603 --> 13:25.338
- THAT TAKES PRIORITY.

13:25.372 --> 13:31.044
BUT IN CASE SOMETHING CHANGES,
I'LL SAVE YOU THE SEAT.

13:31.078 --> 13:33.246
- OKAY.

13:33.280 --> 13:38.251
[moaning]

13:55.635 --> 13:58.105
- HONEY?
- HMM?

13:58.138 --> 14:01.374
- THAT FEELS WONDERFUL.
- I'M GLAD.

14:01.408 --> 14:03.476
- BUT--BUT DO YOU MIND IF WE...

14:03.510 --> 14:05.578
- WHAT?

14:11.418 --> 14:13.086
- IF WE USE THIS?

14:13.120 --> 14:14.988
- GLINDA'S MAGIC WAND?

14:15.022 --> 14:17.958
WE HAVEN'T USED THIS SINCE
DOROTHY WENT HOME TO KANSAS.

14:17.991 --> 14:21.094
- I JUST FELT, I DON'T KNOW,
IN THE MOOD, I GUESS.

14:21.128 --> 14:22.495
BUT IF YOU DON'T WANT TO--

14:22.529 --> 14:23.630
- NO, NO, NO,
IF IT'S WHAT YOU WANT,

14:23.663 --> 14:27.000
THEN LET'S GIVE IT A WHIRL.

14:27.034 --> 14:31.871
[buzzing]

14:36.576 --> 14:38.912
- OH, GOD!

14:38.946 --> 14:42.983
[moaning]

14:43.016 --> 14:45.285
- THERE YOU GO.

14:45.318 --> 14:47.420
- THANKS.

14:49.456 --> 14:51.291
- TAKE IT EASY, DEB.

14:51.324 --> 14:53.626
- YEAH, YOU TOO, BETTY, HONEY.
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

15:07.307 --> 15:11.178
- IN CASE YOU DIDN'T NOTICE,
I WAS IN THE DINER.

15:11.211 --> 15:13.580
- I NOTICED.

15:15.615 --> 15:17.450
- WALK YOU HOME?

15:17.484 --> 15:20.287
- NO, IT'S OKAY.

15:20.320 --> 15:22.289
- IT'S LATE.

15:22.322 --> 15:25.458
- I'VE BEEN DOING IT ON MY OWN
FOR 20 YEARS.

15:25.492 --> 15:27.194
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

15:27.227 --> 15:31.031
- AND YOU'VE GOT A RIGHT HOOK
TO PROVE IT.

15:31.064 --> 15:34.601
[clears throat]

15:34.634 --> 15:36.703
- YOU'RE WORKING LATE.

15:36.736 --> 15:38.338
- JUST GOT TO GET THE JOB DONE.

15:38.371 --> 15:40.573
- USED TO BE THE ONLY REASON
YOU'D STAY UP

15:40.607 --> 15:43.576
WAS BECAUSE IT WAS STILL UP.

15:43.610 --> 15:46.046
- A LOT OF THINGS
"USED TO BE."

15:46.079 --> 15:48.081
- YOU'RE TELLING ME.

15:51.218 --> 15:54.254
- I SHOULDN'T HAVE SAID
WHAT I DID ABOUT VIC.

16:02.129 --> 16:05.598
- YOU'RE DAMN STRAIGHT
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

16:05.632 --> 16:08.335
NOT THAT YOU WERE WRONG.

16:08.368 --> 16:12.072
HE WAS LUCKY
HE GOT THOSE EXTRA YEARS.

16:12.105 --> 16:14.241
BUT IT'S THE WAY YOU SAID IT.

16:14.274 --> 16:16.776
JUST TOSSING IT OFF
LIKE IT DIDN'T MEAN A THING,

16:16.809 --> 16:19.979
LIKE HIS WHOLE FUCKING LIFE
DIDN'T MEAN A THING.

16:24.651 --> 16:26.153
- I SEE YOUR POINT.

16:26.186 --> 16:29.122
- YEAH, SO WHY DIDN'T YOU
SEE IT THEN?

16:32.825 --> 16:37.630
- MAYBE BECAUSE I DIDN'T KNOW
THAT I HAD CANCER THEN.

16:37.664 --> 16:40.633
- WHAT?

16:40.667 --> 16:44.003
- ARE YOU GOING TO MAKE ME
SAY IT TWICE?

16:45.672 --> 16:47.174
- I JUST WANT TO BE SURE
THAT I HEARD--

16:47.207 --> 16:50.177
- YOU HEARD IT.

16:51.278 --> 16:53.580
- SHIT.

16:55.682 --> 16:57.784
ARE YOU OKAY?
- ALL RIGHT?

16:57.817 --> 17:00.553
THEY THINK.

17:00.587 --> 17:04.124
BUT WHO THE HELL KNOWS?

17:04.157 --> 17:05.458
- WELL, THEN WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING

17:05.492 --> 17:07.060
OUT AT 2:00
IN THE MORNING?

17:07.094 --> 17:09.696
YOU SHOULD BE HOME GETTING
YOUR REST, HONEY.

17:09.729 --> 17:11.798
- I CAN'T SLEEP.
I KEEP HAVING THESE DREAMS.

17:11.831 --> 17:13.666
- WELL, FORCE YOURSELF.

17:13.700 --> 17:15.702
AND MAKE SURE YOU EAT,
YOU HEAR ME?

17:15.735 --> 17:18.705
YOU GOT TO KEEP
YOUR STRENGTH UP.

17:20.740 --> 17:23.310
- YES, MOTHER.

17:25.345 --> 17:28.348
- DOES SHE KNOW?

17:30.450 --> 17:33.720
- SO FAR,
JUST MICHAEL AND JUSTIN.

17:33.753 --> 17:36.523
AND...THEODORE.

17:38.491 --> 17:40.160
- AND NOBODY TOLD ME?

17:40.193 --> 17:42.562
- I'M TELLING YOU.

17:42.595 --> 17:44.297
- HOW COME?

17:44.331 --> 17:48.768
- SO THAT YOU'LL FORGIVE ME
AND TAKE PITY ON ME.

17:51.871 --> 17:55.208
- SON OF A BITCH.

18:00.147 --> 18:03.116
YOU'RE GOING TO BE OKAY,
YOU HEAR ME?

18:06.653 --> 18:09.622
YOU'RE GOING TO BE OKAY.

18:18.498 --> 18:19.866
- HEY, I'M MAKING A LIST
FOR THE GROCERY.

18:19.899 --> 18:21.601
TIDE, BUTTER, OATMEAL.

18:21.634 --> 18:22.869
CAN YOU THINK
OF ANYTHING ELSE?

18:22.902 --> 18:25.738
- BATTERIES.
- HUH?

18:25.772 --> 18:27.674
- AFTER LAST NIGHT,
GLINDA'S MAGIC WAND'S

18:27.707 --> 18:28.908
GOING TO NEED RECHARGING.

18:28.941 --> 18:31.778
- OH.
- YOU WERE WILD, HONEY.

18:31.811 --> 18:33.246
- [chuckles]
MEL.

18:33.280 --> 18:34.514
- DON'T BE EMBARRASSED.

18:34.547 --> 18:36.816
IT WAS HOT TO SEE YOU
SO TURNED ON.

18:36.849 --> 18:38.651
- OKAY, WE'RE OUT OF FRUIT.

18:38.685 --> 18:40.220
PEARS, APPLES.

18:40.253 --> 18:41.754
SHOULD I GET MORE BANANAS?

18:41.788 --> 18:42.889
I MEAN...

18:42.922 --> 18:45.625
- I WOULD SAY SO.
- YEAH.

18:45.658 --> 18:47.360
- BY THE WAY,
I TALKED TO DUSTY,

18:47.394 --> 18:49.629
AND SHE SAID THAT WE
CAN DROP GUS OFF AROUND 4:00,

18:49.662 --> 18:51.231
WHICH GIVES US PLENTY OF TIME
TO GET READY

18:51.264 --> 18:52.232
AND GO TO THE OPENING.

18:52.265 --> 18:53.500
- CRANAPPLE JUICE...

18:53.533 --> 18:54.634
- DO YOU WANT TO GO TOGETHER,

18:54.667 --> 18:55.902
OR DO YOU
HAVE TO GET THERE EARLY?

18:55.935 --> 18:57.570
- I DON'T NEED TO BE THERE
AT ALL.

18:57.604 --> 18:58.905
- OH, SO YOU CAN BE A GUEST
JUST LIKE ANYONE ELSE?

18:58.938 --> 19:01.641
- I MEAN,
I'VE DECIDED NOT TO GO.

19:01.674 --> 19:03.276
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
IT'S YOUR SHOW.

19:03.310 --> 19:04.277
YOU PUT THE WHOLE THING
TOGETHER.

19:04.311 --> 19:05.645
- I KNOW.

19:05.678 --> 19:07.247
- WELL,
SO WOULDN'T YOU WANT TO--

19:07.280 --> 19:08.815
- I'VE SPENT ENOUGH TIME
ON IT ALREADY, OKAY?

19:08.848 --> 19:11.251
IT'S TIME I STARTED
BEING MORE ATTENTIVE TO YOU,

19:11.284 --> 19:12.552
TO OUR FAMILY.

19:12.585 --> 19:15.455
MICHAEL EVEN HAD TO GO
TO LAMAZE FOR ME.

19:15.488 --> 19:17.424
- HEY, HEY, HEY, WHEN I
FEEL LIKE I'M NOT GETTING

19:17.457 --> 19:19.792
ENOUGH ATTENTION,
I'LL LET YOU KNOW.

19:19.826 --> 19:22.729
NOW, I WANT YOU TO GO
AND GET SOME OF THE ATTENTION

19:22.762 --> 19:24.864
YOU DESERVE.

19:24.897 --> 19:27.667
- WELL, MAYBE I'LL STOP BY
LATER, WHEN IT'S OVER,

19:27.700 --> 19:30.603
SEE HOW IT WENT.

19:31.904 --> 19:33.873
NOW...

19:33.906 --> 19:36.843
I'M OFF TO THE GROCERY.

19:38.478 --> 19:44.317
[indistinct chatter]

19:44.351 --> 19:45.952
- SINCE WHEN DID TED SCHMIDT,

19:45.985 --> 19:47.954
REIGNING OPERA QUEEN
OF PITTSBURGH,

19:47.987 --> 19:50.723
TRADE IN PUCCINI
FOR PIGSKIN?

19:50.757 --> 19:53.560
- SINCE I TOLD BRIAN I'D HELP
HIM FIND A FAMOUS SPORTS FIGURE

19:53.593 --> 19:55.562
TO MODEL BROWN ATHLETICS'
NEW UNDERWEAR LINE.

19:55.595 --> 19:57.564
- MMM, SOUNDS HOT.

19:57.597 --> 19:59.999
SO, UH, WHICH HUNKY JOCK
DID YOU SELECT

20:00.032 --> 20:02.435
TO DROP TROU AND SMILE
FOR THE BIRDIE?

20:02.469 --> 20:04.003
- I DON'T KNOW
WHO ANY OF THESE GUYS ARE.

20:04.036 --> 20:05.838
- OH, PERHAPS
I CAN HELP YOU OUT.

20:05.872 --> 20:07.907
- YOU?
[scoffs]

20:07.940 --> 20:09.609
LOOK, AT LEAST I KNOW
THE DIFFERENCE

20:09.642 --> 20:11.444
BETWEEN A FOOTBALL,
A BASEBALL, AND A BASKETBALL.

20:11.478 --> 20:14.347
- BALLS ARE BALLS.

20:15.682 --> 20:17.617
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

20:17.650 --> 20:21.388
- WHO?
- DREW BOYD.

20:21.421 --> 20:24.457
STAR QUARTERBACK
FOR THE IRONMEN.

20:24.491 --> 20:26.859
[chuckles]
62% PASS COMPLETIONS.

20:26.893 --> 20:30.029
THREW TWO TOUCHDOWN PASSES
LAST GAME AND RAN FOR TWO.

20:30.062 --> 20:32.031
LED ALL QUARTERBACKS
IN THE LEAGUE IN RUSHING YARDS.

20:32.064 --> 20:33.600
I MEAN, IF HE KEEPS PLAYING
THE WAY HE'S BEEN,

20:33.633 --> 20:34.767
HE'S A CINCH
TO LEAD HIS TEAM

20:34.801 --> 20:36.336
TO A CONFERENCE CHAMPIONSHIP,

20:36.369 --> 20:39.772
THEN TO THE SUPER BOWL.

20:41.408 --> 20:43.343
WHAT?

20:43.376 --> 20:44.744
- HOW DO YOU KNOW ALL THAT?

20:44.777 --> 20:47.480
- HMM, WELL,
LIFE'S FULL OF SURPRISES.

20:47.514 --> 20:48.615
- [laughs]

20:48.648 --> 20:50.016
- HE'S ALSO GORGEOUS.

20:50.049 --> 20:51.884
LOOK AT THAT SMILE

20:51.918 --> 20:54.621
AND THOSE BROAD SHOULDERS

20:54.654 --> 20:57.824
AND THOSE BURLY, BURLY ARMS.

20:57.857 --> 20:59.392
[chuckles]
AND THAT ROCK-HARD BUTT.

20:59.426 --> 21:00.693
- ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

21:00.727 --> 21:03.696
YOU'RE DROOLING
ALL OVER THE MAGAZINE.

21:06.399 --> 21:09.702
WELL, HE IS HOT.

21:09.736 --> 21:12.939
MM, TOO BAD HE'S STRAIGHT.
- MM.

21:12.972 --> 21:16.543
A GIRL CAN ALWAYS DREAM.

21:18.711 --> 21:21.681
[Asian music]

21:21.714 --> 21:29.689
*

21:54.747 --> 21:56.416
- EXCUSE ME.

21:56.449 --> 21:58.885
UH, WE'RE LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING TO...

21:58.918 --> 22:00.453
IMPROVE PERFORMANCE.

22:00.487 --> 22:03.423
- YOU A SINGER?

22:03.456 --> 22:04.691
DANCER?

22:04.724 --> 22:06.359
COMEDIAN?

22:06.393 --> 22:08.761
- UH, NO,
NOT THAT KIND OF PERFORMANCE.

22:08.795 --> 22:12.432
UM, UH...

22:12.465 --> 22:13.633
SEXUAL PERFORMANCE.

22:13.666 --> 22:14.701
- HUH?

22:14.734 --> 22:17.470
- SEXUAL PERFORMANCE.

22:17.504 --> 22:19.739
- SEXUAL?

22:19.772 --> 22:20.973
SEXUAL?

22:21.007 --> 22:23.710
[speaking native language]

22:23.743 --> 22:25.111
- AH, SEXUAL.

22:25.144 --> 22:28.047
[speaking native language]

22:28.080 --> 22:31.851
- OH!
YOU NOT GET HARD?

22:31.884 --> 22:32.985
COME TOO FAST?

22:33.019 --> 22:34.587
- UH, NO, IT'S NOT FOR ME.

22:34.621 --> 22:35.988
IT'S FOR MY FRIEND.

22:36.022 --> 22:39.726
- OH, IT'S WHAT THEY ALL SAY,
HUH?

22:39.759 --> 22:41.127
- WEAK PULSE.

22:41.160 --> 22:42.929
- AH, LOW CHI.

22:42.962 --> 22:46.466
EXHAUSTED CHANG MERIDIAN.

22:46.499 --> 22:49.001
- YOU HAVE DECLINE OF FIRE
IN YOUR GATE OF LIFE,

22:49.035 --> 22:50.537
BUT NO WORRY.

22:50.570 --> 22:53.039
WE MAKE YOU HARD, LIKE ROCK.

22:53.072 --> 22:57.009
- LOOK, I--I TOLD YOU, IT'S--
IT'S FOR SOMEONE ELSE.

22:57.043 --> 22:58.411
- IT'S FOR MY BOYFRIEND.

22:58.445 --> 23:00.079
HE HAD TO HAVE
A TESTICLE REMOVED,

23:00.112 --> 23:01.648
AND THEY GAVE HIM RADIATION.

23:01.681 --> 23:04.617
- OH, CANCER, HUH?

23:04.651 --> 23:06.453
[speaking native language]

23:08.187 --> 23:10.022
- WESTERN MEDICINE.

23:10.056 --> 23:13.092
KILL YOU BEFORE IT CURE YOU.

23:13.125 --> 23:16.028
TOO MUCH WATER,
DROWN OUT HIS FIRE.

23:16.062 --> 23:18.030
- MM.

23:18.064 --> 23:21.434
- VELVET DEER HORN,

23:21.468 --> 23:23.169
CINNAMON BARK.

23:23.202 --> 23:26.105
WARM KIDNEYS.

23:26.138 --> 23:29.175
MORINDA ROOT...
- MM-HMM.

23:29.208 --> 23:32.044
- CHINESE LEEK SEED.

23:32.078 --> 23:34.180
STRENGTHEN YANG.

23:34.213 --> 23:38.985
- THE REHMANNIA ROOT
NOURISH BLOOD,

23:39.018 --> 23:43.189
AND, UH, YEAH, CORNUS FLOWER
MOISTENS YIN, HUH?

23:43.222 --> 23:47.694
- MAKE A TEA.
PLENTY GOOD SEX.

23:49.228 --> 23:51.531
- SEE?
I TOLD YOU.

23:51.564 --> 23:57.504
[both speaking native language]

24:00.573 --> 24:02.008
[both laugh]

24:04.577 --> 24:07.547
[TV on the Radio's Satellite]

24:07.580 --> 24:13.486
[moaning]

24:21.761 --> 24:25.698
- * YOUR VOICE

24:25.732 --> 24:28.701
* WAS A SATELLITE

24:28.735 --> 24:31.003
