25:28.327 --> 25:31.664
- [exhales]

25:32.832 --> 25:37.570
- * WAS THAT BURNING EYE

25:37.604 --> 25:40.306
* WENT WEEPING GAMMA RAYS

25:40.339 --> 25:42.909
- [sighs]

25:42.942 --> 25:43.976
YOUR TURN.

25:44.010 --> 25:46.946
- I'M IN NO HURRY.

25:50.349 --> 25:52.985
DID ANYONE EVER TELL YOU
HOW HOT YOU LOOK IN YOUR UNDIES?

25:53.019 --> 25:54.721
- ABOUT 300 WOMEN.

25:54.754 --> 25:55.922
- HOW MANY MEN?

25:55.955 --> 25:57.790
- [laughs]

25:57.824 --> 25:59.659
- IT'S A SHAME THE REST
OF THE WORLD CAN'T SEE.

25:59.692 --> 26:00.827
- SEE WHAT?

26:00.860 --> 26:02.261
- HOW GORGEOUS YOU ARE.

26:02.294 --> 26:04.130
- CUT IT OUT.
- I'M SERIOUS.

26:04.163 --> 26:07.667
YOU SHOULD DISPLAY
YOUR MANLY CHARMS.

26:07.700 --> 26:09.736
- FLASH MY COCK IN PLAYGIRL?

26:09.769 --> 26:13.205
- I WAS THINKING MORE LIKE,
HMM, UNDERWEAR AD.

26:13.239 --> 26:15.675
- [chuckles]

26:15.708 --> 26:17.209
YOU'RE KIDDING.

26:17.243 --> 26:20.212
- I HAVE THIS FRIEND WHO, UH,
WORKS FOR AN AD AGENCY,

26:20.246 --> 26:21.814
SAYS BROWN ATHLETICS

26:21.848 --> 26:23.883
IS LOOKING
FOR A FAMOUS SPORTS FIGURE

26:23.916 --> 26:26.352
TO BE
THEIR NEW UNDERWEAR MODEL.

26:26.385 --> 26:29.956
AND YOU...
HAVE QUITE THE FIGURE.

26:29.989 --> 26:32.024
- I'M NOT POSING IN MY SHORTS.

26:32.058 --> 26:34.260
EVERYONE WILL THINK
I'M A HOMO.

26:34.293 --> 26:36.362
- WHAT EVERYONE WILL THINK IS,

26:36.395 --> 26:38.765
"I WISH I HAD A BODY LIKE THAT
AND THAT SOMEONE WOULD PAY ME

26:38.798 --> 26:40.833
ALL THAT MONEY
TO SHOW IT OFF."

26:40.867 --> 26:42.368
COME ON.

26:42.401 --> 26:44.403
WHY DON'T YOU POSE?

26:44.436 --> 26:46.372
- HERE?
- WHY NOT?

26:46.405 --> 26:49.375
I'LL SNAP YOUR PICTURE.
- [laughs]

26:49.408 --> 26:51.043
- COME ON.

26:51.077 --> 26:54.046
GIVE IT UP.
SHOW ME WHAT YOU GOT.

26:54.080 --> 26:55.848
OH-HO, YEAH.

26:55.882 --> 26:58.918
THAT'S IT, YEAH.

26:58.951 --> 27:01.921
THAT'S THE TICKET.

27:01.954 --> 27:05.124
HOOO!
HO, HO, HO, YEAH!

27:05.157 --> 27:08.060
GIVE ME SOME OF THAT TRADEMARK
DREW BOYD ACTION.

27:08.094 --> 27:10.129
MAKE LOVE TO THE CAMERA.

27:10.162 --> 27:14.066
YEAH, THAT'S THE WAY.

27:14.100 --> 27:17.704
MAKE ME WANT
TO SUCK YOUR DICK.

27:22.308 --> 27:24.343
- WOULD YOU STOP NAGGING ME
ALREADY?

27:24.376 --> 27:26.913
I'M NOT GOING TO PAY $150
FOR A PAIR OF JEANS.

27:26.946 --> 27:29.816
- DIESEL'S QUALITY, MAN.
- THEY'RE RIPPED FULL OF HOLES.

27:29.849 --> 27:31.751
THEY'RE GOING TO BE RAGS
AFTER TWO WASHINGS.

27:31.784 --> 27:35.888
- PLEASE, DAD?
I MEAN, DUDE.

27:35.922 --> 27:37.690
- THERE YOU ARE.

27:37.724 --> 27:38.691
HURRY UP AND PUT DOWN
YOUR BOOKS,

27:38.725 --> 27:39.926
WE GOT TO GO TO THE MALL.

27:39.959 --> 27:42.228
- YOU KNOW, UH...

27:42.261 --> 27:45.031
IF IT'S OKAY WITH YOU,
UH, I THINK I'LL PASS.

27:45.064 --> 27:47.967
- NO, IT'S NOT OKAY.
WE HAD THIS PLANNED.

27:48.000 --> 27:50.703
- TRASHY MOVIE, GREASY PIZZA,
OVERPRICED CLOTHES.

27:50.737 --> 27:52.071
WHAT MORE CAN A MAN
ASK FOR?

27:52.104 --> 27:53.940
- I-I GOT INVITED
TO A LECTURE.

27:53.973 --> 27:56.075
EDMUND WHITE.
- WHO?

27:56.108 --> 27:58.711
- ONE OF OUR GREATEST
GAY WRITERS.

27:58.745 --> 28:00.913
- WHO INVITED YOU?

28:00.947 --> 28:02.915
- ANTHONY.

28:02.949 --> 28:05.451
- ANTHONY.

28:05.484 --> 28:07.787
- LOOK,
THIS IS IMPORTANT TO ME.

28:07.820 --> 28:09.455
- AND THIS IS IMPORTANT
TO HUNTER.

28:09.488 --> 28:11.457
- IT DOESN'T TAKE TWO OF US
TO BUY HIM A PAIR OF JEANS.

28:11.490 --> 28:12.925
- THAT'S NOT THE POINT.

28:12.959 --> 28:14.326
- HEY, HEY!
IT'S JUST THE MALL.

28:14.360 --> 28:16.395
IN FACT,
HOW ABOUT YOU BOTH NOT GO

28:16.428 --> 28:17.964
AND GIVE ME
YOUR CREDIT CARD?

28:17.997 --> 28:19.465
- THANK YOU
FOR THE THOUGHTFUL SUGGESTION,

28:19.498 --> 28:21.267
BUT, UH, I'M STILL GOING.

28:21.300 --> 28:24.370
I'M SORRY YOU'RE NOT.

28:32.278 --> 28:35.014
- I'M SORRY I'M LATE, SIDNEY,
BUT IT COULDN'T BE HELPED.

28:35.047 --> 28:36.816
GUS GOT A FEVER.
MEL HAD TO WORK LATE.

28:36.849 --> 28:38.084
MY HANDS WERE FULL.

28:38.117 --> 28:39.385
- SO WERE MINE,

28:39.418 --> 28:42.989
ACCEPTING CHECKS,
VISA, OR MASTERCARD.

28:43.022 --> 28:45.024
- THEN IT WAS A SUCCESS?
- AWESOME.

28:45.057 --> 28:46.392
IT'S TOO BAD YOU MISSED IT.

28:46.425 --> 28:48.961
- WHY DON'T YOU GO HOME?
I'LL CLOSE UP.

28:48.995 --> 28:50.162
- DON'T FORGET TO TURN ON
THE ALARM.

28:50.196 --> 28:51.831
- ALL RIGHT.

28:51.864 --> 28:54.266
- SHALL WE GO FOR A DRINK?
- ABSOLUTELY.

28:54.300 --> 28:57.169
- HOW ABOUT JERRY?
- THAT'S A GREAT IDEA.

28:57.203 --> 29:00.139
[door closes]

29:14.153 --> 29:17.456
- [gasps]
OH, MY GOD!

29:17.489 --> 29:18.891
YOU SCARED ME TO DEATH.

29:18.925 --> 29:20.259
- GOOD THING I CAME BACK
FROM THE CAN.

29:20.292 --> 29:21.527
YOU WOULD HAVE LOCKED ME IN.

29:21.560 --> 29:23.896
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

29:23.930 --> 29:26.198
- WELL, I HAD AN OPENING
TONIGHT, IN CASE YOU FORGOT.

29:26.232 --> 29:27.399
- I DIDN'T FORGET.

29:27.433 --> 29:28.467
- THEN WHERE THE HELL WERE YOU?

29:28.500 --> 29:29.936
- I HAD THINGS TO ATTEND TO.

29:29.969 --> 29:31.470
- DON'T GIVE ME THAT SHIT.

29:31.503 --> 29:33.139
THIS WAS THE MOST IMPORTANT
NIGHT OF YOUR LIFE.

29:33.172 --> 29:34.406
- OH, DON'T FLATTER YOURSELF.

29:34.440 --> 29:35.875
- YOUR AUNT MINNIE
COULD'VE DIED,

29:35.908 --> 29:37.009
AND YOU WOULDN'T
HAVE MISSED IT.

29:37.043 --> 29:38.410
- I DON'T HAVE AN AUNT MINNIE.

29:38.444 --> 29:41.013
- YEAH, WELL, I DO,
AND BELIEVE ME,

29:41.047 --> 29:42.815
IF YOU KNEW HER,
IT'S ALL THE MORE REASON

29:42.849 --> 29:45.551
YOU WOULD HAVE BEEN HERE.

29:45.584 --> 29:47.419
SO WHY WEREN'T YOU?
- I ALREADY TOLD YOU.

29:47.453 --> 29:50.522
NOW LET ME LOCK UP,
SO I CAN GO HOME.

29:53.059 --> 29:55.361
- WHAT'S YOUR RUSH?

29:55.394 --> 29:58.164
YOU JUST GOT HERE.
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

29:58.197 --> 30:00.232
- RESPONDING TO MY SENSES.
IT'S WHAT AN ARTIST DOES.

30:00.266 --> 30:02.068
- WELL, TELL YOUR SENSES
TO RESPOND TO THIS:

30:02.101 --> 30:03.335
BACK OFF.

30:03.369 --> 30:05.905
- YOU SURE?

30:05.938 --> 30:07.573
- YES, I'M SURE.
- WELL, I'M NOT.

30:07.606 --> 30:09.909
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I THINK YOU'VE GOT A LOT

30:09.942 --> 30:12.044
OF CONTRADICTORY FEELINGS
GOING ON HERE.

30:12.078 --> 30:13.913
- OH, IS THAT SO?
- YEAH.

30:13.946 --> 30:14.914
I KNEW FROM THE MINUTE
I MET YOU,

30:14.947 --> 30:16.515
YOU WANTED ME TO FUCK YOU.

30:16.548 --> 30:21.053
- WHY, YOU SMUG, ARROGANT--

30:21.087 --> 30:24.957
I WANT YOU TO LEAVE.
NOW!

30:24.991 --> 30:27.526
- SURE.

30:27.559 --> 30:29.328
BUT YOU AIN'T FOOLING ME,
LADY.

30:29.361 --> 30:32.131
MORE IMPORTANT, YOU AIN'T
FOOLING YOURSELF EITHER.

30:32.164 --> 30:34.633
- DON'T YOU DARE TELL ME
HOW I FEEL.

30:34.666 --> 30:36.635
YOU HAVE NO IDEA HOW I FEEL.
- YEAH.

30:36.668 --> 30:38.204
- AND IT ISN'T TRUE
WHAT YOU SAID.

30:38.237 --> 30:40.272
- LIAR, LIAR.

30:40.306 --> 30:41.974
- I HAVE NO FEELINGS FOR YOU.

30:42.008 --> 30:45.844
I MEAN, HOW COULD I?
I'M A LESBIAN.

30:47.513 --> 30:49.982
- THAT'S HOW.

30:52.051 --> 30:57.990
[both moaning]

31:00.392 --> 31:02.394
- OH, GOD.

31:18.177 --> 31:19.445
- OH, GOD.

31:19.478 --> 31:25.417
[both gasping, grunting]

31:33.425 --> 31:35.327
OH, MY GOD!

31:43.369 --> 31:45.037
- HE WAS AMAZING.

31:45.071 --> 31:46.572
AND TO THINK,
I NEVER WOULD'VE HEARD OF HIM

31:46.605 --> 31:48.707
IF IT HADN'T BEEN
FOR YOUR CLASS.

31:48.740 --> 31:54.146
- OH, I'M SURE YOU WOULD'VE
DISCOVERED HIS WORK EVENTUALLY.

31:54.180 --> 31:56.282
- I THOUGHT THE PART
WHERE HE TALKED ABOUT...

31:56.315 --> 31:58.350
HOW BEING POSITIVE
CHANGED HIS LIFE

31:58.384 --> 32:00.619
WAS PARTICULARLY POWERFUL,
DIDN'T YOU?

32:00.652 --> 32:03.022
- HMM.
OH, I'D BETTER NOT.

32:03.055 --> 32:04.623
- AW, COME ON.

32:04.656 --> 32:06.492
GOT TO HELP ME FINISH
THE BOTTLE.

32:06.525 --> 32:10.062
- [sighs]

32:10.096 --> 32:13.632
YOU KNOW, WHAT CONSTANTLY
IMPRESSES AND AMAZES ME,

32:13.665 --> 32:16.435
HOW WHEN CONFRONTED
WITH THE WORST OF CIRCUMSTANCES,

32:16.468 --> 32:20.106
WE, AS GAY MEN, SOMEHOW MANAGE
TO RISE TO THE CHALLENGE.

32:20.139 --> 32:23.575
- LIKE EDMUND WHITE.
- MM-HMM.

32:23.609 --> 32:26.478
- LIKE YOU.

32:34.386 --> 32:38.257
- ANTHONY...

32:38.290 --> 32:41.193
IF THIS IS WHERE ALL THIS
HAS BEEN LEADING,

32:41.227 --> 32:42.728
YOU'VE MADE A MISTAKE.

32:42.761 --> 32:45.631
- I DON'T THINK SO.

32:47.233 --> 32:50.069
- I HAVE A PARTNER.
WE HAVE A FOSTER KID.

32:50.102 --> 32:52.138
- I KNOW,
AND I'M NOT ASKING

32:52.171 --> 32:54.606
FOR ANYTHING I CAN'T HAVE.

32:54.640 --> 32:57.109
ALL I WANT...

32:59.178 --> 33:01.447
IS THIS.

33:03.515 --> 33:05.151
FROM THE MOMENT I SAW YOU,

33:05.184 --> 33:08.387
I FANTASIZED ABOUT YOU...

33:08.420 --> 33:10.389
ADMIRED YOU...

33:15.527 --> 33:18.464
WANTED TO BE LIKE YOU.

33:22.668 --> 33:27.139
THAT'S WHY I WANT YOU
TO GIVE ME THE GIFT.

33:30.609 --> 33:32.644
- WHAT?

33:32.678 --> 33:35.381
- I WANT YOU TO BE THE ONE.

33:35.414 --> 33:38.650
- ANTHONY--
- MAKE ME POSITIVE...

33:38.684 --> 33:40.119
LIKE YOU.

33:40.152 --> 33:41.387
- WHAT ARE YOU--STOP IT!

33:41.420 --> 33:43.122
- IT'S GOING TO HAPPEN ANYWAY.

33:43.155 --> 33:45.391
IT'S JUST A MATTER OF TIME
BEFORE IT DOES.

33:45.424 --> 33:47.393
- NOT IF YOU'RE SAFE.

33:47.426 --> 33:50.796
- WHY BE SAFE?

33:50.829 --> 33:54.733
ALL MY FRIENDS WHO'VE CONVERTED
SAY THEY FEEL LIBERATED.

33:54.766 --> 33:57.269
FREE.

33:57.303 --> 33:59.838
THEY DON'T HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT IT ANYMORE.

33:59.871 --> 34:02.741
IT'S OVER.
DONE.

34:02.774 --> 34:07.213
I WANT TO BE LIKE THEM...

34:07.246 --> 34:09.315
LIKE YOU.

34:13.719 --> 34:17.289
- IT'S LATE.

34:17.323 --> 34:20.259
I HAVE TO GET HOME.

34:27.199 --> 34:31.069
[door opens, closes]

34:57.896 --> 34:59.331
- HERE.

34:59.365 --> 35:01.600
[groans]
DRINK THIS.

35:01.633 --> 35:03.535
- IT SMELLS LIKE YAK SHIT.

35:03.569 --> 35:06.605
- YEAH, I WOULDN'T BE SURPRISED
IF THAT WAS IN IT TOO.

35:06.638 --> 35:10.809
IT'S A MAGIC POTION
FROM A CHINESE HERBALIST.

35:10.842 --> 35:12.478
- WILL IT MAKE ME SMALL?

35:12.511 --> 35:14.213
- I'M HOPING...

35:14.246 --> 35:16.415
THAT IT WILL MAKE YOU LARGE.

35:16.448 --> 35:19.851
VERY, VERY LARGE.

35:35.267 --> 35:38.370
- [groans]

35:38.404 --> 35:39.638
THAT'S DISGUSTING.

35:39.671 --> 35:43.141
- WHO CARES?
AS LONG AS IT WORKS.

35:46.345 --> 35:48.280
- [sighs]

35:58.824 --> 36:01.760
- YOU FEELING ANYTHING?

36:03.695 --> 36:05.597
- WELL, IF YOU'RE EXPECTING
MY GLASSES TO STEAM UP,

36:05.631 --> 36:08.534
I HATE TO DISAPPOINT YOU.

36:08.567 --> 36:11.437
- IT'S SUPPOSED TO REKINDLE
THE FIRE IN YOUR LIFE GATE.

36:11.470 --> 36:13.472
- [scoffs]
MY LIFE GATE?

36:13.505 --> 36:15.674
- I KNOW
IT SOUNDS LUDICROUS, BUT...

36:15.707 --> 36:16.975
IF IT WORKS,
WHO GIVES A SHIT?

36:17.008 --> 36:18.677
- YEAH, WELL,
MAYBE IT CAN ALSO STOP ME

36:18.710 --> 36:20.312
FROM THINKING
ABOUT WHAT'S NO LONGER THERE,

36:20.346 --> 36:23.349
AND THAT IN ITS PLACE
IS THIS PIECE OF PLASTIC.

36:25.317 --> 36:27.486
OR FROM PICTURING THEM
SUCKING A BLOODY,

36:27.519 --> 36:31.757
DISEASE-RIDDEN BALL
OUT OF ME.

36:31.790 --> 36:33.292
OR FROM FEELING SO SHITTY

36:33.325 --> 36:34.760
FROM HAVING THEM
BURN ME TO A CRISP

36:34.793 --> 36:36.295
WITH THEIR RAY GUN
THAT ALL I WANT TO DO

36:36.328 --> 36:38.297
IS DIG A HOLE AND CRAWL IN,

36:38.330 --> 36:41.733
ONLY I'M TOO BUSY VOMITING.

36:43.402 --> 36:45.237
WHO KNOWS?

36:45.271 --> 36:48.840
MAYBE THEN I MIGHT EVEN
BE ABLE TO GET IT UP.

36:48.874 --> 36:52.244
- THERE'S GOT TO BE SOMETHING.

36:52.278 --> 36:57.883
- WHATEVER IT IS,
IT'S NOT A CUP OF LIPTON'S.

37:29.648 --> 37:32.551
- [sighs]

37:33.785 --> 37:36.822
- YOU'RE ALL WET.

37:36.855 --> 37:39.691
HOW WAS THE OPENING?

37:39.725 --> 37:41.427
- IT WAS PRACTICALLY SOLD OUT.

37:41.460 --> 37:43.695
- OH, THAT'S GREAT.

37:43.729 --> 37:45.631
CONGRATULATIONS.

37:45.664 --> 37:47.366
- THANKS.

37:47.399 --> 37:51.670
- AREN'T YOU GLAD
I MADE YOU GO?

38:06.084 --> 38:09.688
- AS YOU KNOW, I DON'T COME HERE
A HELL OF A LOT.

38:09.721 --> 38:10.789
I FIGURE YOU GOT ENOUGH
ON YOUR HANDS

38:10.822 --> 38:13.925
WITHOUT HEARING FROM ME.

38:13.959 --> 38:17.829
BUT, UM, THIS IS IMPORTANT.

38:19.631 --> 38:25.537
IT'S ABOUT MY BROTHER, VIC.
VIC GRASSI.

38:25.571 --> 38:30.342
HE'S GAY, WHICH SEEMS TO, UM,
BOTHER SOME OF THE PEOPLE

38:30.376 --> 38:32.944
YOU GOT WORKING FOR YOU.

38:32.978 --> 38:34.946
BUT I SAY--
[scoffs]

38:34.980 --> 38:36.882
CONSIDERING WHAT'S BEEN GOING
ON IN YOUR CHURCH LATELY,

38:36.915 --> 38:40.018
THEY GOT SOME HELL OF A NERVE
JUDGING OTHERS.

38:44.155 --> 38:48.827
I'M SURE YOU HAVE MORE LOVE
IN YOUR HEART THAN THEY DO...

38:48.860 --> 38:51.430
AND THAT THERE'S
A SPECIAL PLACE IN HEAVEN

38:51.463 --> 38:54.833
JUST FOR VIC.

38:54.866 --> 38:56.902
BUT, UH...

38:56.935 --> 39:01.640
KEEP AN EYE ON HIM,
JUST IN CASE.

39:02.874 --> 39:04.910
ONE MORE THING.

39:04.943 --> 39:07.613
BRIAN KINNEY.

39:07.646 --> 39:12.050
NO DOUBT
YOU'VE HEARD OF HIM.

39:12.083 --> 39:14.586
HE WOULDN'T LIKE ME
TELLING YOU THIS, BUT...

39:14.620 --> 39:19.725
THE BIGGEST ORGAN
HE'S GOT IS HIS HEART.

39:19.758 --> 39:22.994
SO PLEASE, GOD...

39:23.028 --> 39:26.064
MAKE HIM WELL.

39:26.097 --> 39:28.033
PLEASE.

39:31.036 --> 39:32.671
WELL...

39:32.704 --> 39:34.673
I GUESS THAT'S ABOUT IT.

39:34.706 --> 39:37.743
THANKS FOR LISTENING.

39:37.776 --> 39:39.645
AMEN.

39:53.592 --> 39:56.094
JOAN?

39:56.127 --> 39:57.763
IT'S DEBBIE.

39:57.796 --> 39:59.765
DEBBIE NOVOTNY.

39:59.798 --> 40:02.634
- HELLO, DEBBIE.

40:02.668 --> 40:05.771
I'M...
SURPRISED TO SEE YOU HERE.

40:05.804 --> 40:08.206
- WELL, AS I WAS JUST SAYING,
I DON'T STOP BY TOO OFTEN.

40:08.239 --> 40:09.908
BUT WHEN THE GOING
GETS TOUGH,

40:09.941 --> 40:11.577
I STILL HAUL MY ASS
BACK HERE,

40:11.610 --> 40:14.580
YOU KNOW, LIKE
A GOOD LITTLE CATHOLIC GIRL.

40:14.613 --> 40:17.583
- WELL, THAT'S THE BLESSING
OF SUFFERING.

40:17.616 --> 40:19.785
IT BRINGS US CLOSER TO GOD.

40:19.818 --> 40:21.720
- WELL, THAT'S ONE WAY
OF LOOKING AT IT.

40:21.753 --> 40:23.522
ANOTHER WAY IS TO SAY TO HIM,

40:23.555 --> 40:27.192
"COULD YOU CUT IT OUT ALREADY?"

40:27.225 --> 40:29.928
- I HEARD
ABOUT YOUR BROTHER'S PASSING.

40:29.961 --> 40:31.797
PLEASE ACCEPT MY CONDOLENCES.

40:31.830 --> 40:33.565
- THANKS.

40:33.599 --> 40:37.135
- I REMEMBER
WHEN I LOST MY SISTER.

40:37.168 --> 40:40.606
I FELT LIKE I HAD...

40:40.639 --> 40:43.008
LOST MY BEST FRIEND,
MY CONFIDANTE...

40:43.041 --> 40:44.476
[chuckles]

40:44.510 --> 40:45.811
MY WITNESS.

40:45.844 --> 40:48.680
- THAT ABOUT SUMS IT UP.

40:48.714 --> 40:51.550
- WELL, AT LEAST WE HAVE
OUR CHILDREN.

40:51.583 --> 40:53.619
THAT'S SOME COMFORT.

40:53.652 --> 40:57.489
PROVIDED THEY'RE TALKING
TO YOU.

40:57.523 --> 40:59.024
WELL...
[clears throat]

40:59.057 --> 41:02.160
GOD BLESS.

41:02.193 --> 41:05.897
- JOAN.

41:05.931 --> 41:08.967
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU SPOKE TO BRIAN?

41:09.000 --> 41:12.638
- IT'S...BEEN A WHILE.

41:12.671 --> 41:14.906
- WELL, YOU MIGHT WANT
TO GIVE HIM A CALL.

41:14.940 --> 41:18.744
- [scoffs] I DOUBT HE HAS
ANYTHING TO SAY TO ME.

41:18.777 --> 41:22.013
- WELL, THERE MIGHT BE SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO SAY TO HIM.

41:25.016 --> 41:25.984
[beep]

41:26.017 --> 41:27.152
- I GOT HIM.

41:27.185 --> 41:29.888
- GOT WHO?
- DREW BOYD.

41:29.921 --> 41:31.056
HE'S AGREED TO BE
THE NEW UNDERWEAR MODEL

41:31.089 --> 41:32.991
FOR BROWN ATHLETICS.

41:33.024 --> 41:34.259
- THAT'S WONDERFUL, TEDDY.

41:34.292 --> 41:36.762
- [laughs]
IT'S BEYOND WONDERFUL.

41:36.795 --> 41:38.630
IT'S INCREDIBLE.
IT'S ASTONISHING.

41:38.664 --> 41:41.299
IT'S...UNBELIEVABLE.

41:41.332 --> 41:43.001
- IT'S NOT THAT UNBELIEVABLE.

41:43.034 --> 41:45.036
AFTER ALL, THEY ARE PAYING HIM
A MILLION DOLLARS.

41:45.070 --> 41:46.605
- HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

41:46.638 --> 41:49.941
- UH, WELL, THEY ARE,
AREN'T THEY?

41:49.975 --> 41:52.678
- YEAH, BUT--
- WHY ARE YOU SO AMAZED?

41:52.711 --> 41:54.813
- NEVER MIND.

41:54.846 --> 41:57.783
- YOU KNOW, I-I ABSOLUTELY HATE
WHEN YOU DO THAT.

41:57.816 --> 41:59.284
- DO WHAT?

41:59.317 --> 42:01.653
- START TO SAY SOMETHING
AND THEN SAY, "NEVER MIND."

42:01.687 --> 42:02.954
THEN I HAVE TO SPEND
THE NEXT TEN MINUTES

42:02.988 --> 42:04.289
BEGGING YOU TO TELL ME
WHAT IT IS.

42:04.322 --> 42:06.024
- I NEVER KNEW
IT IRRITATED YOU THAT MUCH.

42:06.057 --> 42:07.893
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?
- WELL, WHAT GOOD WOULD IT DO?

42:07.926 --> 42:10.028
YOU'D JUST GET HURT AND SULK.
- I WOULD NOT SULK.

42:10.061 --> 42:11.563
- AND THEN I'D HAVE TO SPEND
ANOTHER TEN MINUTES

42:11.597 --> 42:13.064
CONVINCING YOU
THAT I LOVE YOU

42:13.098 --> 42:14.766
AND BEGGING YOU TO FORGIVE ME,
WHICH YOU FINALLY WOULD.

42:14.800 --> 42:16.635
SO WILL YOU PLEASE JUST TELL ME
WHAT THE FUCK IT IS,

42:16.668 --> 42:20.238
SO WE DON'T HAVE TO GO THROUGH
THE ENTIRE SONG AND DANCE?

42:20.271 --> 42:24.042
- I FORGOT WHAT IT IS
I WASN'T GOING TO TELL YOU.

42:24.075 --> 42:27.345
- YOU WEREN'T GOING TO TELL ME
WHY IT IS SO UNBELIEVABLE

42:27.378 --> 42:31.049
THAT DREWSIE--
D-DREW BOYD SAID YES.

42:31.082 --> 42:33.652
- UH, RIGHT.

42:33.685 --> 42:36.254
BECAUSE I WAS SURE
THAT HE WOULD SAY NO.

42:36.287 --> 42:37.989
THAT HE WOULD
TURN ME DOWN FLAT,

42:38.023 --> 42:39.725
AND THEN I'D HAVE
TO FACE BRIAN'S WRATH

42:39.758 --> 42:41.192
FOR BEING
A WRETCHED FAILURE.

42:41.226 --> 42:44.062
- BUT THAT'S NOT WHAT HAPPENED.
HE SAID YES.

42:44.095 --> 42:46.798
- AND IT'S ALL BECAUSE OF YOU.

42:46.832 --> 42:48.667
- ME? WH--

42:48.700 --> 42:50.201
- WELL, YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO SUGGESTED HIM, AREN'T YOU?

42:50.235 --> 42:53.705
- OH, YEAH, HMM,
I SUPPOSE I DID.

42:53.739 --> 42:55.206
- ALTHOUGH...

42:55.240 --> 42:57.843
I MUST'VE BEEN
PRETTY DAMN IMPRESSIVE

42:57.876 --> 43:01.613
TO CONVINCE A BIG-TIME JOCK
LIKE DREW BOYD

43:01.647 --> 43:05.050
TO STAND AROUND
IN HIS SHORTS.

43:08.119 --> 43:09.955
HUH.

43:09.988 --> 43:12.624
- THERE YOU GO.

43:14.660 --> 43:16.361
PROFESSOR BRUCKNER.
- I'D LIKE TO CHECK THESE OUT.

43:16.394 --> 43:18.096
- CERTAINLY.
- ANTHONY--

43:18.129 --> 43:20.899
- I'M SORRY
ABOUT LAST NIGHT, BEN.

43:20.932 --> 43:23.001
I DIDN'T MEAN TO PUT YOU
IN AN AWKWARD SITUATION.

43:23.034 --> 43:25.771
- IT WASN'T SO MUCH AWKWARD
AS IT WAS UPSETTING

43:25.804 --> 43:27.105
TO LEARN
THAT WHAT YOU REALLY WANTED

43:27.138 --> 43:30.108
WAS FOR ME TO GIVE YOU
"THE GIFT."

43:30.141 --> 43:33.044
- YOU WERE AND STILL ARE
MY INSPIRATION.

43:33.078 --> 43:35.113
- THEN LISTEN TO ME.

43:35.146 --> 43:37.716
YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
IT'S REALLY LIKE TO BE POSITIVE.

43:37.749 --> 43:41.386
NO BOOK, NO LECTURE
COULD EVER DESCRIBE THAT.

43:41.419 --> 43:44.322
SO PLEASE BELIEVE ME WHEN
I TELL YOU YOU DON'T WANT IT.

43:44.355 --> 43:46.391
YOU DON'T.
IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

43:46.424 --> 43:48.994
- WELL, THANKS FOR TRYING
TO TALK ME OUT OF IT,

43:49.027 --> 43:51.129
BUT IT'S TOO LATE.

43:51.162 --> 43:53.064
YOU SEE, I WENT
TO A PARTY LAST NIGHT.

43:53.098 --> 43:55.033
- WHAT KIND OF PARTY?

43:55.066 --> 43:57.002
- IT'S CALLED
A CONVERSION PARTY.

43:57.035 --> 43:59.738
I HAD UNPROTECTED SEX
WITH A DOZEN OR SO GUYS.

43:59.771 --> 44:02.140
IT'S NOT THE WAY
I WOULD'VE PREFERRED IT,

44:02.173 --> 44:05.143
BUT HOPEFULLY,
IT WORKED.

44:05.176 --> 44:06.878
- OH, ANTHONY,
FOR GOD'S SAKE...

44:06.912 --> 44:11.016
- THEY SAID I SHOULD KNOW
IN A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

44:11.049 --> 44:14.185
THE SAME TIME THESE BOOKS
ARE DUE BACK.

44:23.829 --> 44:25.296
- HEY.

44:25.330 --> 44:30.035
- YOUR NEW OFFICE
IS VERY IMPRESSIVE.

44:30.068 --> 44:34.305
AND I LIKE THE NAME,
KINNETIK WITH TWO "N"s.

44:34.339 --> 44:37.943
THAT'S VERY CLEVER.

44:40.011 --> 44:42.814
I'M GLAD TO SEE
YOU'RE DOING SO WELL.

44:44.750 --> 44:47.418
- WELL, THAT MAKES TWO OF US.

44:50.355 --> 44:52.257
- I SAW THAT...

44:52.290 --> 44:55.193
DEBBIE NOVOTNY
IN CHURCH THIS MORNING.

44:55.226 --> 44:56.795
- WELL, WHAT THE HELL
WAS SHE DOING THERE?

44:56.828 --> 45:00.799
- WHAT MOST PEOPLE DO,
PRAY.

45:00.832 --> 45:03.869
[chuckles]
SHE'S QUITE A CHARACTER.

45:03.902 --> 45:05.937
- YEAH, WELL,
I'LL DRINK TO THAT.

45:05.971 --> 45:08.406
- I DON'T KNOW
HOW HER POOR SON EVER SURVIVED.

45:08.439 --> 45:11.843
- MAYBE BECAUSE SHE LOVED HIM.

45:17.182 --> 45:21.086
- AND I LOVE YOU.

45:21.119 --> 45:25.156
WELL, YOU MAY NOT BELIEVE THAT,
BUT IT'S TRUE.

45:25.190 --> 45:29.294
THAT'S WHY IT HURT SO MUCH
THAT I HAD TO HEAR IT FROM HER

45:29.327 --> 45:33.298
AND NOT FROM YOU.

45:33.331 --> 45:36.902
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

45:36.935 --> 45:38.436
- THE REASON BEING?

45:38.469 --> 45:40.171
- SO I COULD HELP YOU.

45:40.205 --> 45:43.842
- WELL, I'M A BIG BOY, MOM.
I CAN DRESS MYSELF.

45:43.875 --> 45:47.846
- I MEANT PRAY FOR YOU.
HELP YOU TO SEE GOD'S PLAN.

45:47.879 --> 45:49.848
- [chuckles]
GOD HAS A PLAN?

45:49.881 --> 45:53.384
- HE SPARED YOU FOR A REASON.
DO YOU KNOW WHY?

45:53.418 --> 45:56.387
- TO TORMENT YOU.

45:56.421 --> 45:58.189
I MEAN, NO MARTYR
WAS EVER SAINTED

45:58.223 --> 46:01.392
WITHOUT GOING THROUGH A SHITLOAD
OF PAIN AND SUFFERING.

46:01.426 --> 46:06.865
WELL, SAINT JOAN,
SAY HELLO TO YOUR SHITLOAD.

46:06.898 --> 46:09.134
- BRIAN.

46:09.167 --> 46:13.939
WHATEVER ANGER,
WHATEVER HATRED YOU HAVE FOR ME,

46:13.972 --> 46:15.807
YOU'RE STILL MY SON,

46:15.841 --> 46:18.209
AND THAT'S WHY I'M TRYING
TO SAVE YOU

46:18.243 --> 46:20.211
FROM THE ETERNAL FIRE.

46:20.245 --> 46:22.280
EVERY TIME YOU ENGAGE
IN BEHAVIOR

46:22.313 --> 46:25.416
THAT THE BIBLE EXPRESSEDLY SAYS
IS AN ABOMINATION,

46:25.450 --> 46:29.054
YOU'RE ADDING ANOTHER ETERNITY
TO YOUR SENTENCE.

46:29.087 --> 46:30.922
- WELL, I WISH
I WAS ENGAGING IN IT.

46:30.956 --> 46:32.590
- IT BRINGS TEARS
TO JESUS' EYES,

46:32.623 --> 46:35.026
KNOWING THAT YOU'VE SINNED.

46:35.060 --> 46:39.464
BUT ONLY YOU CAN SAVE YOURSELF
FROM GOD'S PUNISHMENT.

46:39.497 --> 46:45.070
- YOU THINK GOD GAVE ME CANCER
TO PUNISH ME?

46:48.606 --> 46:50.241
- IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

46:50.275 --> 46:51.977
YOU CAN STILL CHANGE.

46:52.010 --> 46:55.246
I KNOW YOU CAN.

46:55.280 --> 46:57.048
- I CAN?

46:57.082 --> 46:59.117
- THOUGH IT WON'T BE EASY.

46:59.150 --> 47:01.920
YOU'LL HAVE
TO FIGHT TEMPTATION.

47:01.953 --> 47:04.189
BE STRONG.
HARDEN YOURSELF.

47:04.222 --> 47:06.257
- I WANT TO BE HARD, MOM.

47:06.291 --> 47:12.130
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW MUCH I WANT TO BE HARD.

47:12.163 --> 47:14.332
OH, LORD, MAKE ME HARD,

47:14.365 --> 47:20.205
SO THAT I CAN FUCK
EVERY HOT GUY I SEE!

47:20.238 --> 47:23.008
THAT'S WHY GOD
GAVE ME A SECOND CHANCE, MOM,

47:23.041 --> 47:25.076
SO THAT I CAN USE
THE ONE BALL I HAVE LEFT.

47:25.110 --> 47:27.946
- SHAME!

47:27.979 --> 47:29.647
SHAME ON YOU!

47:29.680 --> 47:31.149
- AND IF I HAVE TO SPEND

47:31.182 --> 47:33.551
AN ETERNITY OF ETERNITIES
BURNING IN HELL,

47:33.584 --> 47:35.353
IT'S BETTER
THAN SPENDING ONE GOOD DAY

47:35.386 --> 47:38.990
IN HEAVEN WITH YOU!

48:03.148 --> 48:05.483
[sighs]

48:08.186 --> 48:10.555
THANK YOU.

48:12.357 --> 48:16.027
- SO IN THIS DREAM,
THERE'S THIS GIGANTIC BILLBOARD

48:16.061 --> 48:19.998
OF YOU, TIMES SQUARE,
LIKE, 40 STORIES HIGH,

48:20.031 --> 48:22.300
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR.

48:22.333 --> 48:24.402
- MY AGENT
SAID IT'D BE GREAT EXPOSURE.

48:24.435 --> 48:26.037
- [chuckles]

48:26.071 --> 48:28.539
ANYWAY, YOU KNOW
I HAVE THIS, UM,

48:28.573 --> 48:31.409
LITTLE ECCENTRICITY
ABOUT SIZE,

48:31.442 --> 48:34.012
AND YOUR CROTCH
GOES FROM, LIKE,

48:34.045 --> 48:38.183
THE 16TH TO THE 23RD FLOOR.

48:38.216 --> 48:41.286
SO I GET ON THIS SCAFFOLDING
THAT CONVENIENTLY HAPPENS

48:41.319 --> 48:43.154
TO BE THERE,
PULL MYSELF UP,

48:43.188 --> 48:48.026
AND THE AMAZING THING IS,
THE BILLBOARD COMES TO LIFE.

48:48.059 --> 48:52.297
SO I LEAP OUT ONTO YOUR SHORTS,
PULL THEM DOWN,

48:52.330 --> 48:55.466
AND YOU HAVE
THIS HUMONGOUS BONER

48:55.500 --> 48:59.170
THAT EXTENDS HALFWAY
ACROSS TIMES SQUARE.

48:59.204 --> 49:01.606
SO I CLIMB OUT ONTO IT
TO GIVE YOU A BLOW JOB,

49:01.639 --> 49:05.043
AND I'M HANGING OFF IT--
AHHH--DOING MY THING,

49:05.076 --> 49:08.213
WHEN SUDDENLY,
YOU SHOOT.

49:08.246 --> 49:11.582
OKAY, IT IS LIKE
THIS EXPLODING CASCADE,

49:11.616 --> 49:14.752
AND I RIDE IT...

49:14.785 --> 49:16.721
AND LAND, SAFELY,

49:16.754 --> 49:19.190
IN FRONT
OF THE WINTER GARDEN THEATRE,

49:19.224 --> 49:22.227
WHERE MAMMA MIA!
IS PLAYING.

49:22.260 --> 49:24.062
[chuckles]

49:24.095 --> 49:26.731
- YOU'RE A VERY WEIRD GUY.

49:26.764 --> 49:29.467
- YOU KNOW WHAT
I THINK IT MEANS?

49:29.500 --> 49:31.736
FOR ONE THING, YOU'RE
A BIGGER-THAN-LIFE PERSON.

49:31.769 --> 49:33.204
- GOT IT.

49:33.238 --> 49:36.241
- AND I GUESS
I'M AFRAID THAT...

49:36.274 --> 49:38.609
ONCE THE REST OF THE WORLD
SEES YOU,

49:38.643 --> 49:43.548
I'LL BE JUST ANOTHER FACE
IN THE CROWD.

49:51.822 --> 49:54.392
WHAT'D YOU DO THAT FOR?

49:54.425 --> 49:58.129
- 'CAUSE I WANTED TO.

50:00.198 --> 50:02.100
[In Your Presence playing]

50:02.133 --> 50:05.536
- * IN YOUR PRESENCE

50:05.570 --> 50:08.806
* THERE IS LIFE

50:08.839 --> 50:10.375
- HEY!

50:10.408 --> 50:12.510
MM!

50:12.543 --> 50:14.245
WHAT'S UP?

50:14.279 --> 50:17.782
- IT'S FUNNY YOU SHOULD ASK.

50:17.815 --> 50:19.250
- WHOA!

50:19.284 --> 50:21.652
- IS THAT A THING OF BEAUTY?

50:21.686 --> 50:24.789
- [grunts]
AND A JOY FOREVER.

50:24.822 --> 50:30.328
*

50:30.361 --> 50:35.200
[moaning]

50:35.233 --> 50:39.570
*

50:39.604 --> 50:42.807
SO THAT HAPPY-TIME TEA
ACTUALLY WORKED?

50:42.840 --> 50:46.177
- MMM, UNLIKELY.

50:46.211 --> 50:50.148
- THEN WHENCE THE WOODY?

50:50.181 --> 50:54.719
- LET'S JUST SAY THAT GOD
GAVE ME A SECOND CHANCE.

50:56.187 --> 50:58.289
I DON'T WANT TO BLOW IT.

50:58.323 --> 51:01.692
BUT...
YOU FEEL FREE TO.

51:01.726 --> 51:05.363
- * IN YOUR PRESENCE

51:05.396 --> 51:07.398
* THERE IS LIFE

51:45.636 --> 51:47.272
- WELL?

51:47.305 --> 51:51.276
- YOU SURE YOU WANT MY OPINION
AFTER THE LAST TIME?

51:51.309 --> 51:52.677
- YEAH, I WOULDN'T
HAVE ASKED YOU TO READ IT

51:52.710 --> 51:55.646
IF I DIDN'T.

51:56.814 --> 51:59.250
- OKAY, UM...

51:59.284 --> 52:03.921
MY HONEST OPINION IS...

52:03.954 --> 52:07.525
IT'S BRILLIANT.

52:07.558 --> 52:09.894
I MEAN IT.
- [exhales]

52:09.927 --> 52:12.430
- AT FIRST, I WAS SHOCKED
AND EVEN DISGUSTED

52:12.463 --> 52:15.366
THAT ANYONE WOULD
ACTUALLY WANT TO BE POSITIVE.

52:15.400 --> 52:16.934
BUT SOMEHOW, BY THE END,

52:16.967 --> 52:20.805
I-I REALLY FELT SORRY
FOR THE GUY...

52:20.838 --> 52:23.941
THAT HE COULD BE
THAT LOST...

52:23.974 --> 52:26.344
AND ALONE.

52:30.848 --> 52:34.552
AND IT TAKES
A PRETTY AMAZING WRITER...

52:34.585 --> 52:37.688
TO BE ABLE
TO PULL THAT OFF.

52:40.325 --> 52:43.294
- [chuckles]

53:05.650 --> 53:06.951
SO HOW WAS THE TRIP
TO THE MALL?

53:06.984 --> 53:09.820
[both chuckling]

53:09.854 --> 53:12.890
- I SPLURGED.
I BOUGHT HUNTER HIS JEANS.

53:12.923 --> 53:14.425
- [groans]

53:14.459 --> 53:17.728
- AND HE GOT US SOMETHING,
A CD.

53:17.762 --> 53:19.430
- UH, NOT SOME RAP CRAP.

53:19.464 --> 53:20.998
- NOW, NOW, DEAR.

53:21.031 --> 53:23.468
MUSTN'T CRITICIZE
THE YOUNGER GENERATION'S MUSIC.

53:23.501 --> 53:26.437
- [scoffs]
YEAH.

53:26.471 --> 53:29.440
[Keep the Flame playing]

53:29.474 --> 53:30.575
*

53:30.608 --> 53:32.443
[laughs]

53:32.477 --> 53:34.612
OH, MY--

53:34.645 --> 53:36.747
NOT BAD.

53:36.781 --> 53:39.317
- COME ON, YOU BIG LUG,
WALTZ ME AROUND THE ROOM.

53:39.350 --> 53:42.320
- HMM.

53:42.353 --> 53:44.755
*

53:44.789 --> 53:48.726
- * I JUST CAN'T TELL MYSELF
NOT TO LOVE YOU *

53:48.759 --> 53:50.795
- [laughing]

53:50.828 --> 53:56.767
- * ANY MORE THAN I CAN STOP
MY BEATING HEART *

53:56.801 --> 53:59.404
* EVERY MOMENT I'M AWAKE

53:59.437 --> 54:02.773
* I'M THINKING OF YOU

54:02.807 --> 54:07.378
* AND HOPING
THAT WE'LL NEVER BE APART *

54:07.412 --> 54:08.879
*

54:08.913 --> 54:14.619
* I COULD SAY,
TIME TO GIVE UP THIS FIGHT *

54:14.652 --> 54:16.354
* SURRENDER
TO WHAT'S GONNA BE *

54:16.387 --> 54:18.923
- YOU KNOW WHAT PART
OF YOUR STORY I LIKED BEST?

54:18.956 --> 54:22.493
- HMM?

54:22.527 --> 54:24.662
WHAT?

54:24.695 --> 54:27.064
- THE PART
WHERE THE GIFT-GIVER

54:27.097 --> 54:31.669
DECIDES NOT TO SLEEP
WITH THE BUG-CHASER...

54:31.702 --> 54:34.372
AND GOES BACK
TO HIS PARTNER.

54:34.405 --> 54:39.076
- * AND SO I KEEP THE FAITH
TO BELIEVE LOVE CAN BE TRUE *

54:39.109 --> 54:44.849
* WE MAY TRY TO RUN AWAY,
BUT THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO *

54:44.882 --> 54:47.918
* IF IT'S MEANT TO BE

54:47.952 --> 54:52.923
* THEN THERE'S
ONLY ME AND YOU *

54:52.957 --> 54:57.428
*

54:57.462 --> 55:02.933
* I'LL ALWAYS KEEP THE FLAME

55:02.967 --> 55:08.873
* HOPING YOU FEEL THE SAME

55:08.906 --> 55:13.344
* WHEN I WHISPER YOUR NAME

55:13.378 --> 55:19.350
* IT'S BECAUSE
I'M THINKING OF YOU *

55:19.384 --> 55:21.419
*

55:21.452 --> 55:26.957
* BABY, MY LOVE IS PURE

55:26.991 --> 55:31.095
* I'VE NEVER BEEN MORE SURE

55:31.128 --> 55:33.864
*

55:33.898 --> 55:37.101
* WITHOUT SHAME

55:37.134 --> 55:40.104
* I NOW PROCLAIM

55:40.137 --> 55:44.509
* I WILL ALWAYS

55:44.542 --> 55:50.381
* ALWAYS KEEP THE FLAME

55:50.415 --> 55:58.355
*

56:08.699 --> 56:14.539
* SO MANY ARE DOUBTFUL
AND DESPAIRING *

56:14.572 --> 56:18.943
* MAKING FUN OF THOSE
WHO DARE TO DREAM *

56:18.976 --> 56:20.878
*

56:20.911 --> 56:25.182
* THEY SAY THEY'RE PAST
THE POINT OF EVER CARING *

56:25.215 --> 56:27.017
*

56:27.051 --> 56:32.890
* BUT I KNOW IT'S
NOT AS DARK AS IT MAY SEEM *

56:32.923 --> 56:38.896
* AT THE MOMENT
TROUBLE TRIES TO FIND US *

56:38.929 --> 56:43.768
* AND WE BRACE
AGAINST THE FIERCEST STORM *

56:43.801 --> 56:45.169
*

56:45.202 --> 56:51.041
* IT ONLY TAKES
A TINY SPARK OF KINDNESS *

56:51.075 --> 56:55.713
* TO START A BLAZING FIRE
TO KEEP US WARM *

56:55.746 --> 57:01.185
* I'LL ALWAYS KEEP THE FLAME

57:01.218 --> 57:05.055
* HOPING YOU FEEL THE SAME

57:05.089 --> 57:07.558
*

57:07.592 --> 57:09.594
* WHEN I WHISPER YOUR NAME
